The paper deals with the joint application of representation learning and supervised classification for hyperspectral image analysis. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed involves matrix factorization, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses clustering, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SI.
